Zeta Mu Beta Fraternity, Inc. does not currently have a web site. Communication within the organization is primarily handled through Google Groups and email. Public relations are conducted through Facebook and Twitter, where information about upcoming events is shared with followers and other affiliated individuals or organizations. There is an opportunity to create a web site to allow the organization to share information about itself, spread knowledge about its purpose, and keep the general public informed with news of the fraternity and its activities. This will open up the organization to a worldwide audience, as opposed to communicating on a local or selective basis.

Zeta Mu Beta Fraternity, Inc. does not currently have a web site. Communication within the organization is primarily handled through Google Groups and email. Public relations are conducted through third-party systems such as Facebook and Twitter, where information about upcoming events is shared with followers and other affiliated individuals or organizations. There is an opportunity to create an independent web site to improve the efficiency of such communication processes, opening up the organization to a worldwide audience. The web site shall become the primary system used for publicity and all existing systems shall become supplementary.

Zeta Mu Beta Fraternity, Inc.’s strategic objectives include growth and publicity. The web site project will support these goals by establishing public visibility of the fraternity’s purpose and providing information for prospective members or affiliates. It will also improve publicity by creating a comprehensive source of all matters related to the fraternity and making this available to the general public.
